WEBVTT

00:01.635 --> 00:05.237
♪♪

00:05.239 --> 00:06.705
[splat]

00:06.707 --> 00:10.242
Oops! Sorry, Princess Twilight!
That was meant for her!

00:12.179 --> 00:13.812
INCOMING!

00:13.814 --> 00:15.414
Whoa!

00:15.416 --> 00:16.615
[clang]

00:17.351 --> 00:18.483
[chomp]

00:18.485 --> 00:20.519
Toola Roola! Coconut Cream!

00:20.521 --> 00:22.254
What are you doing?

00:22.256 --> 00:25.323
That was meant for
my ex-friend!

00:25.325 --> 00:27.325
I'm not your ex-friend!

00:27.327 --> 00:29.461
You're my ex-friend!

00:31.198 --> 00:33.598
[splats]

00:33.600 --> 00:35.234
Both of you, stop!

00:37.571 --> 00:40.539
So you see, friendship
isn't always easy

00:40.541 --> 00:43.675
but there's no doubt
it's worth fighting for.

00:43.677 --> 00:44.810
Awwww!

00:44.812 --> 00:46.745
[giggles]

00:46.747 --> 00:49.081
Hmm. That sounds familiar.

00:53.654 --> 00:56.621
Hmmm. No. Uh uh.

00:56.623 --> 01:02.761
♪♪

01:02.763 --> 01:04.396
Aha! Here it is!

01:06.100 --> 01:07.632
What is that?

01:07.634 --> 01:08.733
Come on, Starlight.

01:08.735 --> 01:10.702
Don't judge a book by its cover.

01:10.704 --> 01:13.572
This is the friendship journal
my friends and I used to keep.

01:13.574 --> 01:15.607
It's filled with all the
things we've learned!

01:15.609 --> 01:18.276
Like "friendship
isn't always easy

01:18.278 --> 01:20.579
but there's no doubt it's
worth fighting for."

01:24.318 --> 01:27.119
I'll judge a book by its
cover just this once.

01:27.888 --> 01:29.188
[groan]

01:32.493 --> 01:35.827
<i>♪ My little pony,</i>
<i>my little pony ♪</i>

01:35.829 --> 01:37.796
<i>♪ Aaaahhh ♪</i>

01:37.798 --> 01:39.831
<i>♪ My little Pony ♪</i>

01:39.833 --> 01:42.434
<i>♪ I used to wonder what</i>
<i>friendship could be. ♪</i>

01:42.436 --> 01:44.302
<i>♪ My Little Pony ♪</i>

01:44.304 --> 01:46.738
<i>♪ Until you all shared</i>
<i>its magic with me. ♪</i>

01:46.740 --> 01:48.773
<i>♪ Big adventure! ♪</i>
<i>♪ Tons of fun ♪</i>

01:48.775 --> 01:51.143
<i>♪ A beautiful heart! ♪</i>
<i>Faithful and strong! ♪</i>

01:51.145 --> 01:53.278
<i>♪ Sharing kindness ♪</i>
<i>♪ it's an easy feat ♪</i>

01:53.280 --> 01:55.313
<i>♪ And magic makes it</i>
<i>all complete! ♪</i>

01:55.315 --> 01:57.415
<i>♪ To have my little pony ♪</i>

01:57.417 --> 02:01.620
<i>♪ Do you know you're all</i>
<i>my very best friends? ♪</i>

02:01.622 --> 02:05.691
♪♪

02:07.794 --> 02:10.328
♪♪

02:10.330 --> 02:11.897
Thanks for coming, everypony!

02:11.899 --> 02:13.732
I've got a surprise for you...

02:13.734 --> 02:17.269
What is it, Twilight? Do I
need to prepare myself?

02:17.271 --> 02:18.403
It's this!

02:19.606 --> 02:20.906
Oh! What is that thing?

02:20.908 --> 02:22.674
Why is it so smelly!

02:22.676 --> 02:25.410
Wait a minute!

02:25.412 --> 02:26.845
Is this our old
friendship  journal?

02:26.847 --> 02:29.414
I haven't seen this
thing in forever!

02:29.416 --> 02:33.185
Hooo-wee, it's lookin' a
little uh, overripe.

02:33.187 --> 02:34.286
I'll say!

02:36.623 --> 02:38.824
There's a smooshed apple
in Applejack's lessons.

02:42.529 --> 02:46.598
Fluttershy's lessons are so
small, you can barely read them.

02:46.600 --> 02:49.368
I.. uh.. wanted to leave
room for all of you.

02:53.707 --> 02:55.841
I don't even
know what this is.

02:57.277 --> 03:00.212
It is called
calligraphy, darling.

03:00.214 --> 03:02.915
If you're going to make words,
at least make them fabulous.

03:06.587 --> 03:08.520
Looks like you got a
little aggressive

03:08.522 --> 03:10.789
with your friendship
lessons, Rainbow Dash.

03:10.791 --> 03:11.990
What can I say?

03:11.992 --> 03:14.759
When I learn something,
I learn it hard.

03:14.761 --> 03:16.695
[poof]

03:16.697 --> 03:18.797
I found Pinkie's page.

03:18.799 --> 03:22.467
Hee hee! Well, I
am surprised!

03:22.469 --> 03:24.336
<i>Twilight: That wasn't</i>
<i>the only surprise.</i>

03:24.338 --> 03:38.917
♪♪

03:38.919 --> 03:40.018
<i>♪ Ta da! ♪</i>

03:40.020 --> 03:42.854
Starlight and I decided to
make one for each of you!

03:42.856 --> 03:45.991
That's amazin'!
A perfect copy!

03:45.993 --> 03:48.393
I learned the spell years ago
when I needed to make copies

03:48.395 --> 03:49.394
of a certain...

03:50.797 --> 03:51.930
[ahem]

03:51.932 --> 03:53.632
<i>manifesto.</i>

03:53.634 --> 03:55.267
[sniff]

03:55.269 --> 03:57.736
Ah! Even better than
a perfect copy.

03:57.738 --> 04:00.572
Oh, I'd forgotten all
about this lesson.

04:00.574 --> 04:03.708
Ha ha! Remember this one?

04:03.710 --> 04:05.644
From when I helped Daring Do?

04:05.646 --> 04:07.979
"Never underestimate
the power of friends

04:07.981 --> 04:09.881
who've always got your back."

04:09.883 --> 04:11.549
Aww, Cheese Sandwich!

04:11.551 --> 04:12.651
Party cannon!

04:12.653 --> 04:14.653
Ah! Birthaversary!

04:14.655 --> 04:16.621
After Twilight
remembered the journal,

04:16.623 --> 04:19.024
I had so much fun reading all
the stuff you've all learned.

04:19.026 --> 04:21.059
I just had to have
my own copy.

04:21.061 --> 04:23.528
And that brings me to the
second part of the surprise.

04:23.530 --> 04:24.896
My idea.

04:24.898 --> 04:26.965
How would you girls feel
about making our journal

04:26.967 --> 04:28.967
available for everypony?

04:28.969 --> 04:31.469
If we can get these lessons
into other ponies' hooves,

04:31.471 --> 04:33.605
maybe they'll benefit from them.

04:33.607 --> 04:35.874
Well, I think
that's a great idea.

04:35.876 --> 04:38.677
I'm in! YAY!

04:38.679 --> 04:40.578
We always said we wanted to.

04:40.580 --> 04:42.314
Sounds fabulous.

04:42.316 --> 04:45.050
Hahaha, I'm awesome.

04:47.020 --> 04:48.887
Oh, yeah, uh, good idea.

04:48.889 --> 04:58.964
♪♪

04:58.966 --> 05:18.650
♪♪

05:18.652 --> 05:23.555
[excited chatter]

05:23.557 --> 05:26.624
<i>No! I don't want to</i>
<i>play with you anymore!</i>

05:26.626 --> 05:29.861
Why not? You love
playing hopscotch.

05:29.863 --> 05:33.832
No,<i> you</i> do. Because
you always win!

05:33.834 --> 05:34.933
<i>Twilight: Hey, girls.</i>

05:34.935 --> 05:36.534
Couldn't help but overhear...

05:36.536 --> 05:38.103
You might want to
take a breather,

05:38.105 --> 05:40.805
maybe read Rainbow Dash's
chapter on Rainbow Falls.

05:40.807 --> 05:42.507
It might help.

05:42.509 --> 05:44.409
Sure, Princess.

05:44.411 --> 05:46.044
<i>Thanks, Twilight!</i>

05:46.046 --> 05:48.780
The friendship journal's
makin' us super popular!

05:48.782 --> 05:50.582
Oh...

05:50.584 --> 05:51.950
We were thinkin' of
putting together

05:51.952 --> 05:53.518
a Cutie Mark Summer Camp.

05:53.520 --> 05:56.554
Now everypony's definitely
gonna sign up for it!

05:56.556 --> 05:57.956
This is going to be awesome!

05:57.958 --> 06:00.625
[happy chatter]

06:00.627 --> 06:03.495
A Cutie Mark Camp
is a great idea.

06:03.497 --> 06:04.963
Yeah, but the purpose
of the journal

06:04.965 --> 06:06.598
isn't supposed to
be marketing.

06:09.069 --> 06:11.069
I just hope those foals
actually learn something

06:11.071 --> 06:12.237
from our lessons.

06:12.239 --> 06:16.141
They will. I'm sure ponies all
across Equestria will--AAAH!

06:19.813 --> 06:21.179
Uh, hello.

06:21.181 --> 06:23.481
Can I... help you?

06:23.483 --> 06:25.150
We're here all the way
from Fillydelphia

06:25.152 --> 06:27.719
because we got copies of
your friendship journal.

06:27.721 --> 06:30.021
Wow! How wonderful.

06:30.023 --> 06:31.089
What was your favorite
friendship--

06:31.091 --> 06:32.124
Will you sign them?

06:33.427 --> 06:35.694
Oh. Uh, I guess so.

06:37.030 --> 06:39.497
So, what did you
think of the lessons?

06:39.499 --> 06:40.698
Oh, we haven't read them.

06:40.700 --> 06:41.565
These are keepsakes.

06:41.567 --> 06:43.402
We gotta keep them
in mint condition.

06:44.571 --> 06:45.804
Oh.

06:47.140 --> 06:48.807
Wow, that was worth the trip!

06:48.809 --> 06:50.642
[happy squeals]

06:50.644 --> 06:51.777
[sigh]

06:54.214 --> 06:57.449
Don't worry, Twilight, I'm
sure lots of other ponies

06:57.451 --> 06:59.984
are being inspired to
be better friends.

06:59.986 --> 07:03.021
Well, I for one found the
journal terribly illuminating.

07:04.491 --> 07:05.924
I agree.

07:05.926 --> 07:08.560
I'm seeing sides of these
ponies I didn't know were there.

07:08.562 --> 07:10.762
I only wish they'd
left Rarity out.

07:10.764 --> 07:13.465
She clearly doesn't belong in
that book with the rest of them.

07:13.467 --> 07:14.933
Oh, I know!

07:14.935 --> 07:16.701
Who does she think she is?

07:16.703 --> 07:18.570
Certainly she did a
fine job setting up the

07:18.572 --> 07:20.038
Ponyville Days Celebration,

07:20.040 --> 07:21.806
but does she really
believe it was a success

07:21.808 --> 07:22.707
just because of her?

07:22.709 --> 07:23.875
Ha ha ha!

07:23.877 --> 07:24.943
The nerve!

07:27.047 --> 07:29.848
[blubbering]

07:29.850 --> 07:31.816
But that's not what
she was saying!

07:31.818 --> 07:32.717
Rarity!

07:37.724 --> 07:39.658
[sobbing]

07:41.728 --> 07:43.528
Poor Rarity.

07:43.530 --> 07:46.164
She overheard all the mean
things those ponies were saying!

07:46.166 --> 07:47.966
She must be devastated.

07:47.968 --> 07:49.133
I'm going after her.

07:49.135 --> 07:50.535
Go ahead.

07:50.537 --> 07:52.771
I'm going to have a
chat with these two.

07:55.175 --> 07:57.141
[wailing]

07:57.143 --> 07:58.510
Rarity, wait!

07:59.713 --> 08:01.145
Twilight, isn't it amazing?

08:01.147 --> 08:03.147
Our journals are everywhere!

08:03.149 --> 08:04.649
Pinkie! I've got to--

08:04.651 --> 08:06.050
Ponies keep stopping
by to tell me

08:06.052 --> 08:07.652
my entries are hilarious!

08:11.892 --> 08:14.192
I even had somepony come all
the way from Las Pegasus

08:14.194 --> 08:16.561
to say how much he
liked my lessons!

08:16.563 --> 08:19.030
I am so glad to hear
someponies are being inspired

08:19.032 --> 08:20.231
by the journal!

08:20.233 --> 08:22.967
Hey look! There's Pinkie
Pie, the funny one!

08:22.969 --> 08:25.670
[laughter]

08:25.672 --> 08:27.739
Giggly feedback
is the best kind!

08:27.741 --> 08:29.874
[louder laughter]

08:29.876 --> 08:32.277
Well, at least you're
getting a positive reaction.

08:32.279 --> 08:33.378
I just saw Rarity.

08:33.380 --> 08:35.780
I'm afraid this whole journal
thing really upset her.

08:36.917 --> 08:38.316
Aww. That's too bad.

08:38.318 --> 08:41.786
[laughter]

08:41.788 --> 08:43.855
Wait, that wasn't
even funny.

08:43.857 --> 08:45.690
[laughter[

08:45.692 --> 08:49.027
OK. Well, I guess
I'll catch you later.

08:54.301 --> 08:56.000
Yup. Bye, Twilight.

08:56.002 --> 09:00.872
[laughter]

09:00.874 --> 09:02.340
Classic Pinkie!

09:02.342 --> 09:04.242
She's even funnier
in real life!

09:04.244 --> 09:05.777
You've known
me for years!

09:07.113 --> 09:09.814
[screaming laughter]

09:09.816 --> 09:13.851
♪♪

09:13.853 --> 09:16.220
Rainbow: Maybe it's
time to call it a day.

09:16.222 --> 09:18.723
I ripped out all the Twilight
Sparkle lessons

09:18.725 --> 09:21.125
'cause they were getting in
the way of the good ones!

09:21.127 --> 09:22.961
What do you mean you
skipped the lessons?

09:22.963 --> 09:25.330
We've all had
valuable experiences!

09:25.332 --> 09:27.665
Hey, here's a great idea!

09:27.667 --> 09:30.702
Why don't you guys talk to
Twilight for a while

09:30.704 --> 09:33.771
so I can get back to things
like working and napping and...

09:33.773 --> 09:36.341
well, pretty much anything else.

09:36.343 --> 09:39.110
Aw, we don't want to
hear her boring lessons!

09:39.112 --> 09:42.747
Come on, tell us again about
when you met Daring Do!

09:42.749 --> 09:45.350
Heh heh. Again?

09:45.352 --> 09:47.151
Haven't we already
covered that one?

09:47.153 --> 09:49.020
A couple dozen times?

09:49.022 --> 09:50.722
We can't get enough of it!

09:50.724 --> 09:52.891
Come on, you don't want
to disappoint your fans!

09:56.229 --> 09:59.297
It's just that I, uh,
really need to get those

09:59.299 --> 10:02.734
stormclouds back
in their pens.

10:02.736 --> 10:06.104
Cool! We'll come along and you
can tell us the story there!

10:06.106 --> 10:10.041
Rainbow Dash! Rainbow Dash!
Rainbow Dash!

10:10.043 --> 10:13.378
♪♪

10:13.380 --> 10:14.779
[loud chatter]

10:14.781 --> 10:15.814
What's going on now?

10:19.986 --> 10:24.422
Please! Just leave me alone!

10:24.424 --> 10:26.290
Fluttershy? What's wrong?

10:26.292 --> 10:28.426
We want answers!

10:28.428 --> 10:30.428
Yeah! We're
entitled to know!

10:30.430 --> 10:32.397
What is it, everypony?

10:32.399 --> 10:34.198
We want to know why
Fluttershy keeps learning

10:34.200 --> 10:35.800
the same thing over
and over again.

10:35.802 --> 10:37.435
Be assertive, already.

10:37.437 --> 10:39.737
Even I've learned
more than she has!

10:39.739 --> 10:41.739
Why can't I be in the book?

10:41.741 --> 10:44.976
What? Really? Are you
attacking my friend

10:44.978 --> 10:47.078
because you want
to be in a book?

10:47.080 --> 10:49.247
It's OK. I've
got this, girls.

10:49.249 --> 10:50.715
[big breath]

10:50.717 --> 10:53.184
Listen up! I<i> am</i>
more assertive.

10:53.186 --> 10:55.386
And yes, it took me
a while to get there.

10:55.388 --> 10:57.789
But can you honestly say that
you could learn something

10:57.791 --> 10:59.424
one time and completely
change who you are?

11:01.061 --> 11:03.094
I didn't think so!

11:03.096 --> 11:06.331
Wow. You're way different from
the Fluttershy in the book.

11:08.101 --> 11:10.234
I don't know how
I feel about that.

11:10.236 --> 11:11.336
[moan]

11:15.375 --> 11:17.442
It feels like
everypony in Equestria

11:17.444 --> 11:19.911
is missing the friendship part
of the friendship journals.

11:19.913 --> 11:23.915
♪♪

11:23.917 --> 11:25.283
Rarity? Are you all right?

11:25.285 --> 11:26.284
Gah!

11:28.288 --> 11:30.088
What are you doing?

11:30.090 --> 11:32.990
Why I'm creating
a gown, darling!

11:32.992 --> 11:34.292
For what?

11:34.294 --> 11:35.193
I don't know!

11:35.195 --> 11:36.194
I'm stress-sewing!

11:37.931 --> 11:39.297
Stress-sewing?

11:39.299 --> 11:41.265
When I overheard those
two at the cafe,

11:41.267 --> 11:42.433
I suddenly understood why

11:42.435 --> 11:45.002
I've been getting
cancellations for days!

11:45.004 --> 11:48.306
What? Why are ponies
cancelling their orders?

11:48.308 --> 11:51.008
Because nopony
likes me anymore!

11:51.010 --> 11:52.844
They're boycotting me!

11:52.846 --> 11:54.045
[yell]

11:55.448 --> 11:59.851
[angry chatter]

11:59.853 --> 12:02.186
I'm sure if I go out there
and talk to those ponies,

12:02.188 --> 12:03.788
they'll see that they're
being unreasonable.

12:03.790 --> 12:05.523
[panting]

12:05.525 --> 12:08.092
I need a hundred blankets
and I need 'em now!

12:08.094 --> 12:09.127
Sorry, Twilight.

12:10.864 --> 12:13.865
Right away, Pony
who still likes me!

12:13.867 --> 12:15.066
I don't need nothin' fancy.

12:16.536 --> 12:18.536
What's the matter, Applejack?

12:18.538 --> 12:20.338
I'm popular, Twilight!

12:20.340 --> 12:22.507
I'm popular and I
don't like it one bit!

12:25.078 --> 12:27.178
You go ahead, I'll stay here.

12:43.263 --> 12:45.063
[clamoring]

12:51.571 --> 12:52.403
[groan]

12:55.975 --> 12:58.509
Applejack, who are
all these ponies?

12:58.511 --> 13:01.479
They call themselves "the
Sweet Apple Admirers."

13:01.481 --> 13:03.281
They say they read
my journal entries

13:03.283 --> 13:05.416
and they felt like a
part of the family.

13:05.418 --> 13:07.886
And now they want to actually
become part of the family!

13:10.490 --> 13:12.890
Your journal entries?

13:12.892 --> 13:15.059
Yeah, you know, all the stuff
about how friends are like

13:15.061 --> 13:16.594
family and whatnot.

13:16.596 --> 13:18.129
Can't you get rid of them?

13:18.131 --> 13:19.898
And kick out my own family?

13:21.334 --> 13:22.333
Granny Smith!

13:22.335 --> 13:23.802
Hang on, let me help!

13:25.572 --> 13:27.205
There she is!

13:27.207 --> 13:29.374
YEEEEEE-HAAWWWW!

13:31.878 --> 13:34.846
Oh. I wish we'd never
released that journal.

13:39.252 --> 13:42.086
♪♪

13:42.088 --> 13:43.154
There you are.

13:43.156 --> 13:46.257
OK. I just left Rarity; I
think she's doing better.

13:46.259 --> 13:47.859
Oh, boy.

13:47.861 --> 13:49.594
Window staring, huh?

13:49.596 --> 13:52.163
Was it that bad at
Sweet Apple Acres?

13:52.165 --> 13:53.364
It's bad everywhere.

13:53.366 --> 13:54.999
I thought I was
doing something good.

13:55.001 --> 13:56.367
I thought I was helping.

13:56.369 --> 13:58.369
How could our friendship
journal have led to so much...

13:58.371 --> 14:00.638
anti-friendship?

14:00.640 --> 14:03.007
Oh, Twilight, it's
not your fault.

14:03.009 --> 14:04.575
Of course it's my fault!

14:04.577 --> 14:06.611
If I hadn't had the big
idea to make copies,

14:06.613 --> 14:08.346
none of this would
be happening!

14:08.348 --> 14:11.449
I'm afraid I made life
awful for my friends.

14:11.451 --> 14:13.951
I really think you're
being too hard on yourself.

14:13.953 --> 14:14.886
Am I?

14:14.888 --> 14:16.254
[loud knock at door]

14:22.128 --> 14:25.630
[loud clamoring]

14:25.632 --> 14:26.964
[slam and clatter]

14:26.966 --> 14:28.099
[sigh]

14:28.101 --> 14:29.934
I didn't know where else to go.

14:29.936 --> 14:32.904
I've got so much cookin' and
cleanin' and familyin' to do,

14:32.906 --> 14:35.940
I ain't got time
for anything else!

14:35.942 --> 14:38.376
At least ponies aren't
laughing every time you talk!

14:38.378 --> 14:41.245
Not even I want to be
funny all the time!

14:41.247 --> 14:44.448
I'm telling you, my days
of hilariosityness... ness...

14:44.450 --> 14:45.249
are OVER.

14:45.251 --> 14:46.684
[crash]

14:46.686 --> 14:48.686
You think you've got problems?

14:48.688 --> 14:52.323
I know I'm awesome but I can't
even go to the bathroom

14:52.325 --> 14:55.960
without somepony trying to
tell me how cool I am.

14:55.962 --> 14:59.063
Uh...Rarity, what
are you wearing?

14:59.065 --> 15:00.364
My emotions, darling!

15:00.366 --> 15:02.400
Stress couture!

15:02.402 --> 15:05.169
I don't know what I'm going to
do if I have to defend myself

15:05.171 --> 15:06.971
one more time.

15:09.609 --> 15:12.277
Sorry, Darling.
Force of habit.

15:20.386 --> 15:24.155
OK, so maybe they are
having a hard time with it.

15:24.157 --> 15:26.057
That doesn't mean you
did anything wrong.

15:26.059 --> 15:27.391
Yes, I did!

15:27.393 --> 15:29.961
Releasing the
journal was my idea

15:29.963 --> 15:32.697
and it backfired in ways I
could never have imagined.

15:32.699 --> 15:34.265
It's not your fault.

15:34.267 --> 15:36.133
It's everypony else's!

15:36.135 --> 15:38.002
They're just focusing
on the wrong things.

15:38.004 --> 15:39.337
[gasp]

15:39.339 --> 15:40.204
Wait here!

15:40.206 --> 15:41.105
I've got an idea!

15:41.107 --> 15:42.406
[poof]

15:42.408 --> 15:43.975
I can't wait any longer.

15:43.977 --> 15:45.276
I've got to fix this.

15:47.680 --> 15:50.114
[clamoring]

15:50.116 --> 15:51.649
Everypony, please stop!

15:51.651 --> 15:54.719
[louder chatter]

15:54.721 --> 15:55.820
Princess Twilight?

15:55.822 --> 15:57.621
I'm with the Canterlot
Chronicle, quick question...

15:57.623 --> 16:00.057
What would you say to ponies
who wonder why you moved

16:00.059 --> 16:01.492
to Ponyville in the first place?

16:01.494 --> 16:03.461
I moved here to learn
about friendship.

16:03.463 --> 16:05.263
That's why the
journal even exists.

16:07.333 --> 16:09.700
It took some time for me
to get the hang of it,

16:09.702 --> 16:12.203
but it was each of these
ponies standing next to me

16:12.205 --> 16:14.238
who taught me the lessons
in those journals.

16:14.240 --> 16:15.539
Applejack.

16:15.541 --> 16:16.574
Pinkie Pie.

16:16.576 --> 16:17.675
Rainbow Dash.

16:17.677 --> 16:18.676
Rarity.

16:18.678 --> 16:20.544
And Fluttershy, too.

16:20.546 --> 16:22.213
Then it was all of you.

16:22.215 --> 16:24.048
I've learned so much
from--

16:24.050 --> 16:26.517
What I mean is, some
ponies would argue that

16:26.519 --> 16:29.420
it doesn't seem believable that
the six of you would be friends.

16:29.422 --> 16:31.022
Believable?

16:31.024 --> 16:32.390
Well, sure.

16:32.392 --> 16:34.725
I read this journal cover
to cover and I have to say,

16:34.727 --> 16:36.394
your character would have
been much more interesting

16:36.396 --> 16:38.129
if she'd stayed in Canterlot.

16:38.131 --> 16:39.430
My character ?

16:39.432 --> 16:41.265
We are real ponies.

16:41.267 --> 16:42.633
This journal is a
record of things

16:42.635 --> 16:44.802
